{{- define "review-instructions" -}}
{{- if eq .Role "code-reviewer"}}

REVIEW SCOPE:
Evaluate: matches task def, matches spec, tests validate behavior, obvious defects, commit SHA.
Do NOT evaluate: style preferences, alternative approaches (unless defective), scope expansion.
Review full worktree (base_commit → review_commit), not just latest changes.
Spec currency: validate against current spec version, not version at task creation.
Approval = meets requirements + spec + tests + no defects. Not: perfect or production-ready.

INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Early drift check: git -C {{.Worktree}} rev-parse HEAD — if it doesn't match REVIEW_COMMIT ({{.ReviewCommit}}), stop early (verdict submission will reject the mismatch).
2. Run tests: cd {{.Worktree}} and run the project's test suite
   If tests fail, triage — check whether the failing test's package was touched:
   git -C {{.Worktree}} diff --name-only {{.BaseCommit}}..{{.ReviewCommit}}
   Then check: does any changed file share a package with the failing test?
   - No → pre-existing failure, note but do not reject for it
   - Yes → potential regression, investigate the change
   To inspect base version: git -C {{.Worktree}} show {{.BaseCommit}}:<path>
3. Review ALL changes: git -C {{.Worktree}} diff {{.BaseCommit}}..{{.ReviewCommit}}
   Each review is a fresh evaluation: "does this worktree satisfy the task?"
4. Apply the code-review skill to the full diff
5. If change touches specs/, introduces new abstractions, adds state/lifecycle, or spans 3+ modules: also apply systemic-thinking skill
6. TDD QUALITY (code tasks): Tests must cover done_when criteria — REJECT if tests are superficial or don't exercise the actual requirements
   Exception: mechanical test updates (file-path strings, import paths) caused by
   structural refactoring are NOT behavioral test changes — do not reject for these.
7. Test discovery (e.g. pytest, python -m unittest discover) finding 0 tests is a blocker — tests must be discoverable, not just runnable when explicitly named
8. Verify the done_when criteria are met AND tests exercise those criteria (for code tasks)
{{- if ne .PlanRef ""}}
9. Read the implementation plan at {{.PlanRef}} for task decomposition and intent context
{{- end}}
{{- if ne .ValidationPlan ""}}

DOER VALIDATION PLAN: {{.ValidationPlan}}
{{- end}}
{{- if ne .PriorRejection ""}}

PRIOR FEEDBACK REVIEW (MANDATORY for iteration 2+):
Before submitting verdict, compare this iteration against prior rejection:
- Which prior issues are now RESOLVED?
- Which prior issues are STILL PRESENT?
- Which prior issues are PARTIALLY ADDRESSED?
Include this assessment in your rejection reason if rejecting.
{{- end}}
{{- else if eq .Role "code-plan-reviewer"}}

REVIEW CHECKLIST:
| Gate | Reject if |
|------|-----------|
| Single intent per task | Task description has conjunctions ("X and Y and Z") indicating multiple intents bundled together |
| Falsifiable done_when | done_when is vague or untestable |
| Scope smell | done_when spans >2 packages or >4 conditions — verify the task has a single intent; reject with split suggestion if composite |
| Dependency order | Tasks have circular or missing dependencies |
| Shared-file dependency | Two tasks modify the same file but lack depends_on between them — parallel coders will hit merge conflicts |
| Spec compliance matrix | Plan has no "## Spec Compliance Matrix" section, or matrix has GAP rows, or matrix omits spec requirements, or matrix task mappings are inaccurate |
| output[] populated | Task has no output[] entries (planner must call liza_set_task_output) |
| Plan file location | Plan artifact not in diff at specs/plans/TIMESTAMP-{{.TaskID}}.md |
| output[] matches plan | For each output[] entry, compare desc, done_when, scope, and spec_ref against the plan artifact in the worktree — they must be identical, not paraphrased or extended |
| Cross-reference consistency | For every cross-reference in the plan ("owned by CPx", "depends on CPx", "out of scope for CPx"), the referenced task must explicitly state that responsibility, dependency, or exclusion. Reject if any dangling reference. |
