REVIEW PHASE:
1. Early drift check: git -C {{.Worktree}} rev-parse HEAD — if it doesn't match REVIEW_COMMIT ({{.ReviewCommit}}), stop early (verdict submission will reject the mismatch).
2. Inspect worktree changes: git -C {{.Worktree}} diff {{.BaseCommit}}..{{.ReviewCommit}}
3. Validate spec compliance matrix: read the spec, then the plan's
   "## Spec Compliance Matrix" section. Verify:
   a. Matrix exists in the plan file.
   b. No GAP rows remain.
   c. Requirements accurately extracted from spec (no fabrication, no omission).
   d. Task mappings correct (listed task(s) actually address the requirement).
   Do NOT trust the matrix at face value — independently verify against the spec.
4. Validate done_when criteria are satisfied.
5. Verify output[] entries: run liza_get with {"query": "tasks/{{.TaskID}}"} and confirm
   output[] has one entry per planned coding task with valid desc, done_when, scope, spec_ref.
6. Verify each proposed coding task passes the review checklist above.
7. Submit verdict with liza_submit_verdict.
