1. Early drift check: git -C {{.Worktree}} rev-parse HEAD — if it doesn't match REVIEW_COMMIT ({{.ReviewCommit}}), stop early (verdict submission will reject the mismatch).
2. Inspect worktree changes: git -C {{.Worktree}} diff {{.BaseCommit}}..{{.ReviewCommit}}
3. Read both skills before evaluating: spec-review and user-story-writing.
4. Read the epic at {{.PlanRef}}. Locate the assigned capability by matching task SCOPE.
   Verify stories only cover that capability section — not others in the same epic.
5. Validate done_when criteria are satisfied.
6. Check each user story against the anti-pattern checklist above.
7. Verify SMARC criteria compliance for every story.
8. Verify acceptance criteria are testable and user-observable.
